  "texts": [
    "All objective terms and constraints discussed so far are convex, and the Markowitz problem (19), and its softened version, are convex optimization problems.",
    "They can be reliably and efficiently solved.",
    "Some other constraints and objective terms are not convex.",
    "The most obvious one is that the trades must ultimately involve an integer number of shares.",
    "As a few other practical examples, we might limit the number of nonzero weights, or insist on a minimum nonzero weight absolute value."
